;s:0:\"\";s:9:\"menu_icon\";a:2:{s:4:\"type\";s:9:\"dashicons\";s:5:\"value\";s:20:\"dashicons-admin-post\";}s:19:\"rename_capabilities\";b:0;s:24:\"singular_capability_name\";s:4:\"post\";s:22:\"plural_capability_name\";s:5:\"posts\";s:8:\"supports\";a:6:{i:0;s:5:\"title\";i:1;s:6:\"author\";i:2;s:6:\"editor\";i:3;s:9:\"revisions\";i:4;s:9:\"thumbnail\";i:5;s:13:\"custom-fields\";}s:10:\"taxonomies\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"has_archive\";b:0;s:16:\"has_archive_slug\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"rewrite\";a:4:{s:17:\"permalink_rewrite\";s:13:\"post_type_key\";s:10:\"with_front\";s:1:\"1\";s:5:\"feeds\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"pages\";s:1:\"1\";}s:9:\"query_var\";s:13:\"post_type_key\";s:14:\"query_var_name\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"can_export\";b:1;s:16:\"delete_with_user\";b:0;s:20:\"register_meta_box_cb\";s:0:\"\";s:16:\"enter_title_here\";s:0:\"\";s:15:\"show_in_graphql\";i:1;s:19:\"graphql_single_name\";s:5:\"event\";s:19:\"graphql_plural_name\";s:6:\"events\";}','Events','events','publish','closed','closed','','post_type_67c9818d16c53','','','2025-03-06 11:11:57','2025-03-06 11:11:57','',0,'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=acf-post-type&#038;p=6',0,'acf-post-type','',0),(7,1,'2025-03-06 11:11:23','2025-03-06 11:11:23','a:12:{s:8:\"location\";a:1:{i:0;a:1:{i:0;a:3:{s:5:\"param\";s:9:\"post_type\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";s:5:\"value\";s:5:\"event\";}}}s:8:\"position\";s:6:\"normal\";s:5:\"style\";s:7:\"default\";s:15:\"label_placement\";s:3:\"top\";s:21:\"instruction_placement\";s:5:\"label\";s:14:\"hide_on_screen\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"show_in_rest\";i:0;s:15:\"show_in_graphql\";i:1;s:18:\"graphql_field_name\";s:6:\"events\";s:37:\"map_graphql_types_from_location_rules\";i:0;s:13:\"graphql_types\";s:0:\"\";}','Events','events','publish','closed','closed','','group_67c98272aed81','','','2025-03-06 15:03:25','2025-03-06 15:03:25','',0,'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=acf-field-group&#038;p=7',0,'acf-field-group','',0),(8,1,'2025-03-06 11:11:23','2025-03-06 11:11:23','a:14:{s:10:\"aria-label\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"type\";s:11:\"date_picker\";s:12:\"instructions\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"required\";i:0;s:17:\"conditional_logic\";i:0;s:7:\"wrapper\";a:3:{s:5:\"width\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"class\";s:0:\"\";s:2:\"id\";s:0:\"\";}s:14:\"display_format\";s:5:\"d/m/Y\";s:13:\"return_format\";s:5:\"d/m/Y\";s:9:\"first_day\";i:1;s:17:\"allow_in_bindings\";i:1;s:15:\"show_in_graphql\";i:1;s:19:\"graphql_description\";s:0:\"\";s:18:\"graphql_field_name\";s:4:\"date\";s:16:\"graphql_non_null\";i:0;}','Date','date','publish','closed','closed','','field_67c982723ae10','','','2025-03-06 14:58:46','2025-03-06 14:58:46','',7,'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=acf-field&#038;p=8',0,'acf-field','',0),(10,1,'2024-03-06 11:12:57','2024-03-06 11:12:57','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Join us for a day of delicious food, live music, and fun activities at the annual</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Summer Food Festival','','publish','closed','closed','','summer-food-festival','','','2025-03-06 16:52:01','2025-03-06 16:52:01','',0,'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=event&#038;p=10',0,'event','',0),(11,1,'2025-03-06 11:12:09','2025-03-06 11:12:09','{\"version\": 3, \"isGlobalStylesUserThemeJSON\": true }','Custom Styles','','publish','closed','closed','','wp-global-styles-twentytwentyfive','','','2025-03-06 11:12:09','2025-03-06 11:12:09','',0,'http://localhost:8888/?p=11',0,'wp_global_styles','',0),(12,1,'2025-03-06 11:12:56','2025-03-06 11:12:56','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is a sample event.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','My Sample Event','','inherit','closed','closed','','10-revision-v1','','','2025-03-06 11:12:56','2025-03-06 11:12:56','',10,'http://localhost:8888/?p=12',0,'revision','',0),(14,1,'2024-11-22 14:08:54','2024-11-22 14:08:54','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There’s something truly magical about the Alps. Stretching across eight countries, this iconic mountain range offers an incredible mix of natural beauty, adventure, and cultural richness. Whether you’re a seasoned hiker or just someone looking to soak in stunning views, the Alps never disappoint. From the rugged peaks of the French Alps to the lush meadows in Switzerland, every corner offers something unique.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the best ways to experience the Alps is by exploring its many hiking trails. Popular routes like the Tour du Mont Blanc take you through charming villages, glacial valleys, and panoramic ridges that feel like they belong in a postcard. Even outside of peak hiking season, the Alps offer year-round beauty, with winter bringing world-class skiing and cozy alpine lodges where you can unwind after a day outdoors.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Beyond the scenery, the culture of the Alps is equally captivating. You’ll find local festivals celebrating mountain life, hearty cuisine like fondue and schnitzel, and a deep-rooted connection between the people and the land. Whether you’re admiring the sunrise over snow-capped peaks or sharing stories with fellow travelers in a rustic cabin, exploring the Alps is about so much more than just the views — it’s about embracing a way of life shaped by the mountains themselves.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Best time to visit: June to September for hiking, </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>December to March for skiing</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Must-see spots: Zermatt, Chamonix, Dolomites, Innsbruck</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Recommended gear:</strong> Sturdy boots, waterproof layers, and a good cameraLocal tip: Try a mountain hut stay for an authentic alpine experience</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Exploring the Alps','','publish','open','open','','exploring-the-alps','','','2025-03-06 16:53:57','2025-03-06 16:53:57','',0,'http://localhost:8888/?p=14',0,'post','',0),(16,1,'2024-09-29 14:18:55','2024-09-29 14:18:55','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Paris 2024 Summer Olympics were filled with unforgettable moments that captured the hearts of millions around the world. From historic achievements to stunning performances, the Games showcased the pinnacle of athleticism. One of the standout moments was the debut of <strong>surfing</strong> as an Olympic sport, with athletes carving up the waves at Teahupo’o in Tahiti, delivering thrilling competition and showcasing a unique blend of athleticism and artistry. The waves provided a perfect backdrop for surfers to make their mark on Olympic history.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Another unforgettable moment came during the <strong>athletics</strong> events, where <strong>French sprinter Marie-José Pérec</strong> made a spectacular return to the track, securing a gold medal in the 400m. Her victory was a triumph not just for her, but for the host nation, as the French crowd erupted in cheers. Additionally, the men’s <strong>basketball final</strong>, where the U.S. team battled it out against France, delivered heart-stopping moments of skill, intensity, and national pride, ending with the U.S. team taking home the gold in a thrilling finish.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But it wasn’t just about the big names and marquee events; the Paris 2024 Olympics offered a platform for rising stars in lesser-known sports. The electric atmosphere at the <strong>equestrian events</strong> and the emotional celebrations in <strong>synchronized swimming</strong> reminded everyone of the diverse talent the Games bring to the global stage. With Paris\' unique charm as the backdrop, the 2024 Olympics were a truly spectacular showcase of sporting excellence.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Top Moments from Paris Olympics 2024','','publish','open','open','','top-moments-from-paris-olympics-2024','','','2025-03-06 15:07:19','2025-03-06 15:07:19','',0,'http://localhost:8888/?p=16',0,'post','',0),(17,1,'2024-10-17 14:17:08','2024-10-17 14:17:08','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Asia is home to some of the most breathtaking beaches in the world, each offering its own unique blend of natural beauty and local culture. From the powdery white sands of the Philippines to the dramatic cliffs of Thailand, these beaches aren’t just postcard-perfect — they’re gateways to unforgettable experiences. Whether you’re after vibrant coral reefs for snorkeling or secluded coves for quiet reflection, Asia’s shores have something for every kind of traveler.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One must-see destination is <strong>White Beach</strong> in Boracay, Philippines, known for its crystal-clear waters and lively beachfront scene. For a more off-the-beaten-path experience, <strong>Radhanagar Beach</strong> on Havelock Island in India’s Andaman archipelago offers pristine sands backed by lush rainforest. Meanwhile, <strong>Railay Beach</strong> in Thailand enchants visitors with its towering limestone cliffs, accessible only by boat, creating a sense of tropical seclusion even though it’s just a short hop from Krabi.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Beyond their natural beauty, these beaches are windows into the vibrant coastal cultures of Asia. From fresh seafood cooked right on the sand to local festivals that light up the shoreline, each beach tells its own story. Whether you’re chasing sunsets, exploring underwater worlds, or simply unwinding with your toes in the sand, Asia’s beaches are more than destinations — they’re experiences that stay with you long after you’ve left the shore.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','5 Stunning Beaches in Asia','','publish','open','open','','5-stunning-beaches-in-asia','','','2025-03-06 15:07:23','2025-03-06 15:07:23','',0,'http://localhost:8888/?p=17',0,'post','',0),(18,1,'2025-07-18 14:20:26','2025-07-18 14:20:26','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In today’s world, many people struggle with getting a good night’s rest, and often, stress and anxiety are the culprits. Yoga offers a natural way to relax both the mind and body, making it an excellent tool for improving sleep quality. Simple poses, like <strong>Child’s Pose</strong> and <strong>Legs Up the Wall</strong>, activate the parasympathetic nervous system, which helps to reduce stress and promote a sense of calm. The deep breathing techniques that accompany yoga practice also encourage a shift from the “fight or flight” mode to a restful state, allowing the body to wind down before bed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition to its calming benefits, yoga for sleep is about consistency. Incorporating a gentle <strong>yoga routine</strong> into your evening ritual can create a peaceful transition from the hustle of the day to a restful night. Poses such as <strong>Reclining Bound Angle</strong> and <strong>Cat-Cow Stretch</strong> can help release physical tension that might otherwise keep you awake. The slow, deliberate movements give your body a chance to let go of built-up stress, while the focus on breath helps clear the mind from overthinking.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For those who find it difficult to disconnect, a regular yoga practice can be a game-changer. Over time, the practice helps you tune in to your body’s natural rhythms and signals, making it easier to fall asleep and stay asleep throughout the night. Whether practiced as a full 30-minute session or a simple 10-minute wind-down, yoga is an effective, natural way to encourage better sleep without relying on medications or external aids.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Yoga for Better Sleep','','private','open','open','','yoga-for-better-sleep','','','2025-03-06 16:52:16','2025-03-06 16:52:16','',0,'http://localhost:8888/?p=18',0,'post','',0),(19,1,'2024-05-28 14:28:19','2024-05-28 14:28:19','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Training for a marathon is as much a mental challenge as it is a physical one. Whether you’re a beginner or someone looking to improve your time, building a solid training plan is essential. Most plans span <strong>16 to 20 weeks</strong>, gradually increasing your mileage while balancing rest and recovery. Long runs, usually done once a week, are the backbone of marathon training — they prepare your body to endure the race distance while teaching you important lessons about pacing and nutrition.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition to long runs, a good marathon plan should include <strong>easy runs</strong>, <strong>speed work</strong>, and <strong>cross-training</strong> to build endurance, speed, and overall strength. Incorporating rest days is just as crucial as the workouts themselves — giving your body time to recover helps prevent injury and burnout. Nutrition also plays a major role in training, with <strong>carbohydrates</strong> providing essential fuel for long runs and <strong>protein</strong> aiding muscle repair.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Finally, marathon training isn’t just about running; it’s about <strong>mental preparation</strong>. Learning to manage discomfort, stay motivated on tough days, and build confidence in your ability to go the distance are all part of the process. Whether your goal is to finish strong or achieve a personal best, training with patience, consistency, and self-belief will help you cross that finish line with pride.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','How to Train for a Marathon','','publish','open','open','','how-to-train-for-a-marathon','','','2025-03-06 16:54:46','2025-03-06 16:54:46','',0,'http://localhost:8888/?p=19',0,'post','',0),(20,1,'2025-03-03 14:30:09','2025-03-03 14:30:09','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Minimalism at home isn’t just about owning fewer things — it’s about creating a space that feels calm, intentional, and free from unnecessary clutter. By simplifying your surroundings, you create more room for what truly matters, whether that’s quality time with family, hobbies you love, or simply a clearer mind. The process often starts with <strong>decluttering</strong>, removing items that no longer serve a purpose, and carefully curating what you choose to keep. This doesn’t mean stripping your home of personality, but rather making sure every item has meaning or function.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once the clutter is gone, <strong>designing a minimalist space</strong> becomes easier. Clean lines, neutral colors, and thoughtful storage can all help maintain the sense of simplicity. It’s not about perfection — it’s about being intentional with your space so your home feels like a retreat rather than a source of stress. Minimalism at home also encourages <strong>mindful consumption</strong>, helping you think twice before bringing new items into your space, which creates a long-term habit of living lighter.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Minimalism at Home','','publish','open','open','','minimalism-at-home','','','2025-03-06 16:53:08','2025-03-06 16:53:08','',0,'http://localhost:8888/?p=20',0,'post','',0),(21,1,'2025-03-06 14:08:54','2025-03-06 14:08:54','Post content about the Alps and beautiful scenery.','Exploring the Alps','','inherit','closed','closed','','14-revision-v1','','','2025-03-06 14:08:54','2025-03-06 14:08:54','',14,'http://localhost:8888/?p=21',0,'revision','',0),(24,1,'2025-03-06 14:13:08','2025-03-06 14:13:08','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There’s something truly magical about the Alps. Stretching across eight countries, this iconic mountain range offers an incredible mix of natural beauty, adventure, and cultural richness. Whether you’re a seasoned hiker or just someone looking to soak in stunning views, the Alps never disappoint. From the rugged peaks of the French Alps to the lush meadows in Switzerland, every corner offers something unique.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the best ways to experience the Alps is by exploring its many hiking trails. Popular routes like the Tour du Mont Blanc take you through charming villages, glacial valleys, and panoramic ridges that feel like they belong in a postcard. Even outside of peak hiking season, the Alps offer year-round beauty, with winter bringing world-class skiing and cozy alpine lodges where you can unwind after a day outdoors.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Beyond the scenery, the culture of the Alps is equally captivating. You’ll find local festivals celebrating mountain life, hearty cuisine like fondue and schnitzel, and a deep-rooted connection between the people and the land. Whether you’re admiring the sunrise over snow-capped peaks or sharing stories with fellow travelers in a rustic cabin, exploring the Alps is about so much more than just the views — it’s about embracing a way of life shaped by the mountains themselves.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Best time to visit: June to September for hiking, </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>December to March for skiing</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Must-see spots: Zermatt, Chamonix, Dolomites, Innsbruck</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Recommended gear:</strong> Sturdy boots, waterproof layers, and a good cameraLocal tip: Try a mountain hut stay for an authentic alpine experience</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Exploring the Alps','','inherit','closed','closed','','14-revision-v1','','','2025-03-06 14:13:08','2025-03-06 14:13:08','',14,'http://localhost:8888/?p=24',0,'revision','',0),(25,1,'2025-03-06 14:17:08','2025-03-06 14:17:08','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Asia is home to some of the most breathtaking beaches in the world, each offering its own unique blend of natural beauty and local culture. From the powdery white sands of the Philippines to the dramatic cliffs of Thailand, these beaches aren’t just postcard-perfect — they’re gateways to unforgettable experiences. Whether you’re after vibrant coral reefs for snorkeling or secluded coves for quiet reflection, Asia’s shores have something for every kind of traveler.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One must-see destination is <strong>White Beach</strong> in Boracay, Philippines, known for its crystal-clear waters and lively beachfront scene. For a more off-the-beaten-path experience, <strong>Radhanagar Beach</strong> on Havelock Island in India’s Andaman archipelago offers pristine sands backed by lush rainforest. Meanwhile, <strong>Railay Beach</strong> in Thailand enchants visitors with its towering limestone cliffs, accessible only by boat, creating a sense of tropical seclusion even though it’s just a short hop from Krabi.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Beyond their natural beauty, these beaches are windows into the vibrant coastal cultures of Asia. From fresh seafood cooked right on the sand to local festivals that light up the shoreline, each beach tells its own story. Whether you’re chasing sunsets, exploring underwater worlds, or simply unwinding with your toes in the sand, Asia’s beaches are more than destinations — they’re experiences that stay with you long after you’ve left the shore.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','5 Stunning Beaches in Asia','','inherit','closed','closed','','17-revision-v1','','','2025-03-06 14:17:08','2025-03-06 14:17:08','',17,'http://localhost:8888/?p=25',0,'revision','',0),(26,1,'2025-03-06 14:18:55','2025-03-06 14:18:55','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Paris 2024 Summer Olympics were filled with unforgettable moments that captured the hearts of millions around the world. From historic achievements to stunning performances, the Games showcased the pinnacle of athleticism. One of the standout moments was the debut of <strong>surfing</strong> as an Olympic sport, with athletes carving up the waves at Teahupo’o in Tahiti, delivering thrilling competition and showcasing a unique blend of athleticism and artistry. The waves provided a perfect backdrop for surfers to make their mark on Olympic history.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Another unforgettable moment came during the <strong>athletics</strong> events, where <strong>French sprinter Marie-José Pérec</strong> made a spectacular return to the track, securing a gold medal in the 400m. Her victory was a triumph not just for her, but for the host nation, as the French crowd erupted in cheers. Additionally, the men’s <strong>basketball final</strong>, where the U.S. team battled it out against France, delivered heart-stopping moments of skill, intensity, and national pride, ending with the U.S. team taking home the gold in a thrilling finish.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But it wasn’t just about the big names and marquee events; the Paris 2024 Olympics offered a platform for rising stars in lesser-known sports. The electric atmosphere at the <strong>equestrian events</strong> and the emotional celebrations in <strong>synchronized swimming</strong> reminded everyone of the diverse talent the Games bring to the global stage. With Paris\' unique charm as the backdrop, the 2024 Olympics were a truly spectacular showcase of sporting excellence.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Top Moments from Paris Olympics 2024','','inherit','closed','closed','','16-revision-v1','','','2025-03-06 14:18:55','2025-03-06 14:18:55','',16,'http://localhost:8888/?p=26',0,'revision','',0),(27,1,'2025-03-06 14:20:26','2025-03-06 14:20:26','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In today’s world, many people struggle with getting a good night’s rest, and often, stress and anxiety are the culprits. Yoga offers a natural way to relax both the mind and body, making it an excellent tool for improving sleep quality. Simple poses, like <strong>Child’s Pose</strong> and <strong>Legs Up the Wall</strong>, activate the parasympathetic nervous system, which helps to reduce stress and promote a sense of calm. The deep breathing techniques that accompany yoga practice also encourage a shift from the “fight or flight” mode to a restful state, allowing the body to wind down before bed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition to its calming benefits, yoga for sleep is about consistency. Incorporating a gentle <strong>yoga routine</strong> into your evening ritual can create a peaceful transition from the hustle of the day to a restful night. Poses such as <strong>Reclining Bound Angle</strong> and <strong>Cat-Cow Stretch</strong> can help release physical tension that might otherwise keep you awake. The slow, deliberate movements give your body a chance to let go of built-up stress, while the focus on breath helps clear the mind from overthinking.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For those who find it difficult to disconnect, a regular yoga practice can be a game-changer. Over time, the practice helps you tune in to your body’s natural rhythms and signals, making it easier to fall asleep and stay asleep throughout the night. Whether practiced as a full 30-minute session or a simple 10-minute wind-down, yoga is an effective, natural way to encourage better sleep without relying on medications or external aids.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Yoga for Better Sleep','','inherit','closed','closed','','18-revision-v1','','','2025-03-06 14:20:26','2025-03-06 14:20:26','',18,'http://localhost:8888/?p=27',0,'revision','',0),(29,1,'2025-03-06 14:28:19','2025-03-06 14:28:19','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Training for a marathon is as much a mental challenge as it is a physical one. Whether you’re a beginner or someone looking to improve your time, building a solid training plan is essential. Most plans span <strong>16 to 20 weeks</strong>, gradually increasing your mileage while balancing rest and recovery. Long runs, usually done once a week, are the backbone of marathon training — they prepare your body to endure the race distance while teaching you important lessons about pacing and nutrition.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition to long runs, a good marathon plan should include <strong>easy runs</strong>, <strong>speed work</strong>, and <strong>cross-training</strong> to build endurance, speed, and overall strength. Incorporating rest days is just as crucial as the workouts themselves — giving your body time to recover helps prevent injury and burnout. Nutrition also plays a major role in training, with <strong>carbohydrates</strong> providing essential fuel for long runs and <strong>protein</strong> aiding muscle repair.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Finally, marathon training isn’t just about running; it’s about <strong>mental preparation</strong>. Learning to manage discomfort, stay motivated on tough days, and build confidence in your ability to go the distance are all part of the process. Whether your goal is to finish strong or achieve a personal best, training with patience, consistency, and self-belief will help you cross that finish line with pride.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','How to Train for a Marathon','','inherit','closed','closed','','19-revision-v1','','','2025-03-06 14:28:19','2025-03-06 14:28:19','',19,'http://localhost:8888/?p=29',0,'revision','',0),(31,1,'2025-03-06 14:30:09','2025-03-06 14:30:09','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Minimalism at home isn’t just about owning fewer things — it’s about creating a space that feels calm, intentional, and free from unnecessary clutter. By simplifying your surroundings, you create more room for what truly matters, whether that’s quality time with family, hobbies you love, or simply a clearer mind. The process often starts with <strong>decluttering</strong>, removing items that no longer serve a purpose, and carefully curating what you choose to keep. This doesn’t mean stripping your home of personality, but rather making sure every item has meaning or function.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once the clutter is gone, <strong>designing a minimalist space</strong> becomes easier. Clean lines, neutral colors, and thoughtful storage can all help maintain the sense of simplicity. It’s not about perfection — it’s about being intentional with your space so your home feels like a retreat rather than a source of stress. Minimalism at home also encourages <strong>mindful consumption</strong>, helping you think twice before bringing new items into your space, which creates a long-term habit of living lighter.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Minimalism at Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','20-revision-v1','','','2025-03-06 14:30:09','2025-03-06 14:30:09','',20,'http://localhost:8888/?p=31',0,'revision','',0),(32,1,'2025-03-06 14:30:27','2025-03-06 14:30:27','','Blog','','publish','closed','closed','','blog','','','2025-03-06 14:30:27','2025-03-06 14:30:27','',0,'http://localhost:8888/?page_id=32',0,'page','',0),(33,1,'2025-03-06 14:30:17','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2025-03-06 14:30:17','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://localhost:8888/?p=33',0,'post','',0),(34,1,'2025-03-06 14:30:27','2025-03-06 14:30:27','','Blog','','inherit','closed','closed','','32-revision-v1','','','2025-03-06 14:30:27','2025-03-06 14:30:27','',32,'http://localhost:8888/?p=34',0,'revision','',0),(35,1,'2025-03-06 14:31:11','2025-03-06 14:31:11','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>...or something like this:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Home Page','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2025-03-06 14:31:11','2025-03-06 14:31:11','',2,'http://localhost:8888/?p=35',0,'revision','',0),(36,1,'2025-03-06 14:34:51','2025-03-06 14:34:51','<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Who we are</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>Our website address is: http://localhost:8888.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Comments</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>When visitors leave comments on the site we collect the data shown in the comments form, and also the visitor&#8217;s IP address and browser user agent string to help spam detection.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An anonymized string created from your email address (also called a hash) may be provided to the Gravatar service to see if you are using it. The Gravatar service privacy policy is available here: https://automattic.com/privacy/. After approval of your comment, your profile picture is visible to the public in the context of your comment.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Media</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>If you upload images to the website, you should avoid uploading images with embedded location data (EXIF GPS) included. Visitors to the website can download and extract any location data from images on the website.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Cookies</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>If you leave a comment on our site you may opt-in to saving your name, email address and website in cookies. These are for your convenience so that you do not have to fill in your details again when you leave another comment. These cookies will last for one year.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you visit our login page, we will set a temporary cookie to determine if your browser accepts cookies. This cookie contains no personal data and is discarded when you close your browser.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you log in, we will also set up several cookies to save your login information and your screen display choices. Login cookies last for two days, and screen options cookies last for a year. If you select &quot;Remember Me&quot;, your login will persist for two weeks. If you log out of your account, the login cookies will be removed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you edit or publish an article, an additional cookie will be saved in your browser. This cookie includes no personal data and simply indicates the post ID of the article you just edited. It expires after 1 day.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Embedded content from other websites</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>Articles on this site may include embedded content (e.g. videos, images, articles, etc.). Embedded content from other websites behaves in the exact same way as if the visitor has visited the other website.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These websites may collect data about you, use cookies, embed additional third-party tracking, and monitor your interaction with that embedded content, including tracking your interaction with the embedded content if you have an account and are logged in to that website.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Who we share your data with</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>If you request a password reset, your IP address will be included in the reset email.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How long we retain your data</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>If you leave a comment, the comment and its metadata are retained indefinitely. This is so we can recognize and approve any follow-up comments automatically instead of holding them in a moderation queue.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For users that register on our website (if any), we also store the personal information they provide in their user profile. All users can see, edit, or delete their personal information at any time (except they cannot change their username). Website administrators can also see and edit that information.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What rights you have over your data</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>If you have an account on this site, or have left comments, you can request to receive an exported file of the personal data we hold about you, including any data you have provided to us. You can also request that we erase any personal data we hold about you. This does not include any data we are obliged to keep for administrative, legal, or security purposes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Where your data is sent</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>Visitor comments may be checked through an automated spam detection service.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n','Privacy Policy','','inherit','closed','closed','','3-revision-v1','','','2025-03-06 14:34:51','2025-03-06 14:34:51','',3,'http://localhost:8888/?p=36',0,'revision','',0),(37,1,'2025-03-06 14:35:31','2025-03-06 14:35:31','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Welcome to our corner of the internet — a space where curiosity, creativity, and community come together. We’re a passionate team of writers, creators, and explorers who believe in the power of storytelling to connect people. Whether we’re diving into the best travel destinations, exploring wellness tips, or sharing advice on everyday life, our goal is to inspire, inform, and spark conversations.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What started as a small project has grown into a vibrant platform covering a wide range of topics — from mental health and fitness to food, culture, and beyond. We’re not experts in everything, but we’re lifelong learners who love digging into subjects that matter to you. Our content is designed to be both <strong>useful</strong> and <strong>relatable</strong>, blending practical tips with personal experiences to help you navigate life with a bit more ease and inspiration.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','About Us','','publish','closed','closed','','about-us','','','2025-03-06 14:35:31','2025-03-06 14:35:31','',0,'http://localhost:8888/?page_id=37',0,'page','',0),(38,1,'2025-03-06 14:34:55','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2025-03-06 14:34:55','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://localhost:8888/?p=38',0,'post','',0),(39,1,'2025-03-06 14:35:31','2025-03-06 14:35:31','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Welcome to our corner of the internet — a space where curiosity, creativity, and community come together. We’re a passionate team of writers, creators, and explorers who believe in the power of storytelling to connect people. Whether we’re diving into the best travel destinations, exploring wellness tips, or sharing advice on everyday life, our goal is to inspire, inform, and spark conversations.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What started as a small project has grown into a vibrant platform covering a wide range of topics — from mental health and fitness to food, culture, and beyond. We’re not experts in everything, but we’re lifelong learners who love digging into subjects that matter to you. Our content is designed to be both <strong>useful</strong> and <strong>relatable</strong>, blending practical tips with personal experiences to help you navigate life with a bit more ease and inspiration.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','About Us','','inherit','closed','closed','','37-revision-v1','','','2025-03-06 14:35:31','2025-03-06 14:35:31','',37,'http://localhost:8888/?p=39',0,'revision','',0),(40,1,'2025-03-06 14:37:54','2025-03-06 14:37:54','<!-- wp:navigation-link {\"label\":\"Blog\",\"url\":\"#\",\"kind\":\"custom\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:navigation-link {\"label\":\"About\",\"url\":\"#\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:navigation-link {\"label\":\"FAQs\",\"url\":\"#\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:navigation-link {\"label\":\"Authors\",\"